<subSubSection id="DF2C0913564A42705C4EE14E283412E0" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" type="notes">
<paragraph id="649198B4873E91A97AA264468C9C8B9B" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E28E6597BB2EA3CD174A70A5D72CFA89" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">
Species complex. The taxonomy of the species is confused, with a long list of synonyms. Originally described from the Northern Adriatic but reported from worldwide locations (
<bibRefCitation id="64B2D7E9E71E812B16F00BEEC288F50B" author="Martin, Daniel" journalOrPublisher="Hydrobiologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="145 - 162" title="Inter-population variability and character description in the sponge-associated Haplosyllisspongicola complex (Polychaeta: Syllidae)" volume="496" year="2003">
<normalizedToken id="7B2B04753F699B5DBBC1FE6D1A0E2223" originalValue="Martín">Martin</normalizedToken>
et al. 2003
</bibRefCitation>
), with three different morphotypes in the Western Mediterranean. Currently, three well-described species of 
<taxonomicName id="314C5F34E821F2A707D2EA2A126CB1A3" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Haplosyllis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haplosyllis" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">Haplosyllis</taxonomicName>
are known the Mediterranean: 
<taxonomicName id="927EBEB7D55387E967EF7FDDCB869650" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Haplosyllis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haplosyllis spongicola" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="spongicola">Haplosyllis spongicola</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="7E2AA8327942ABA648F3541DF84D7669" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Haplosyllis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haplosyllis" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">Haplosyllis</taxonomicName>
chamaeleon Laubier, 1960 and 
<taxonomicName id="886B2BFD9A99BA23ED2EB8D13351DBA4" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Haplosyllis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haplosyllis granulosa" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="granulosa">Haplosyllis granulosa</taxonomicName>
(Lattig, San 
<normalizedToken id="BDCF9168A6CA1260DF4F2C6B7D98B6D0" originalValue="Martín">Martin</normalizedToken>
&amp; Martin, 2007). The description of 
<taxonomicName id="B7300F3ED2B477CEF38DD9AEA0AFA376" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Haplosyllis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haplosyllis spongicola" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="spongicola">Haplosyllis spongicola</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="17B44BD41425D2F09A51CAFFB8027916" author="San Martin, G." journalOrPublisher="Fauna Iberica" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination=": 544 pp" title="AnnelidaPolychaeta II: Syllidae. In: Ramos MA, et al. (Eds)" volume="21, Museo Nacional de Ciencias Naturales, CA, SAIC, Madrid" year="2003">
San 
<normalizedToken id="BC5FCF5F2E76C0EBECC1169203036900" originalValue="Martín">Martin</normalizedToken>
(2003)
</bibRefCitation>
is referred in part to 
<taxonomicName id="5079A8FEB0B14BF5EFC00D4B2ED510CA" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Haplosyllis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haplosyllis granulosa" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="granulosa">Haplosyllis granulosa</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="89B44825370E2F4C7008D9F079A3044B" author="Lattig, Patricia" journalOrPublisher="Scientia Marina" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="551 - 570" title="Taxonomic and morphometric analyses of the Haplosyllisspongicola complex (Polychaeta: Syllidae: Syllinae) from Spanish seas, with re-description of the type species and descriptions of two new species" volume="71" year="2007">Lattig et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
). In addition, a number of 
<taxonomicName id="594E53CF2480546BAEC6AA289D670D9F" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Haplosyllis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haplosyllis" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">Haplosyllis</taxonomicName>
species have been described from the Mediterranean and the Black Sea which are currently regarded as incertae sedis due to lost type material and insufficient descriptions (
<bibRefCitation id="C183BF212F172DAFE3BD7CD346250D34" author="Lattig, Patricia" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="1 - 40" title="A taxonomic revision of the genus Haplosyllis Langerhans, 1887 (Polychaeta, Syllidae, Syllinae)" volume="2220" year="2009">
Lattig and 
<normalizedToken id="0F682216983A3838B380A8ED3B44A10C" originalValue="Martín">Martin</normalizedToken>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
). Eastern Mediterranean records should also be examined for possible occurrences of the Red Sea species 
<taxonomicName id="40AC876EFF4727266676726099EECB94" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Haplosyllis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haplosyllis djiboutiensis" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="djiboutiensis">Haplosyllis djiboutiensis</taxonomicName>
Gravier, 1900.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
